ZH: 我不喜欢在工作场所讨论私事。
EN: I don't like discussing personal matters in the workplace.

ZH: 请不要打扰我，我有一些私事要处理。
EN: Please don't disturb me, I have some personal matters to attend to.

ZH: 私事不应该被公开讨论。
EN: Personal matters should not be publicly discussed.

ZH: 我们尽量避免谈论私事。
EN: We try to avoid discussing personal matters.

ZH: 不要过问我的私事。
EN: Don't pry into my personal matters.

ZH: 每个人都有自己的私事，不要过度关心。
EN: Everyone has their own personal matters, don't be overly concerned.

ZH: 让我们专注于工作，而不是私事。
EN: Let's focus on work instead of personal matters.

ZH: 我和同事之间不讨论私事。
EN: I don't discuss personal matters with colleagues.

ZH: 他不擅长处理私事。
EN: He's not good at handling personal matters.

ZH: 我的私事不需要你干涉。
EN: My personal matters don't need your interference.

ZH: 请尊重我的私事隐私。
EN: Please respect my privacy regarding personal matters.

ZH: 私事不应该成为工作中的话题。
EN: Personal matters should not be a topic of discussion at work.

ZH: 我们应该保护他人的私事。
EN: We should protect other people's personal matters.

ZH: 我只分享私事给亲近的朋友。
EN: I only share personal matters with close friends.

ZH: 他对别人的私事非常感兴趣。
EN: He is very interested in other people's personal matters.

ZH: 我不希望私事影响到我的职业生涯。
EN: I don't want personal matters to affect my career.

ZH: 请不要插手我的私事。
EN: Please don't meddle in my personal matters.

ZH: 我们应该尊重他人的私事。
EN: We should respect other people's personal matters.

ZH: 我愿意听你的私事，如果你想分享的话。
EN: I'm willing to listen to your personal matters if you want to share.

ZH: 我们应该学会区分工作和私事。
EN: We should learn to differentiate between work and personal matters.
